b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. CodeGPT is best suited for developers wanting LLM flexibility, VS Code users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Mutable AI, meanwhile, shines for auto generating documentation, codebase understanding, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, CodeGPT describes itself as \"Connect any AI model to your code editor.\" Mutable AI, established in 2021, positions itself as \"AI-accelerated software development and documentation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **CodeGPT** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (6 vs 5), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Mutable AI is a poor choice — far from it. Mutable AI excels in its own right, particularly for auto generating documentation and codebase understanding.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value multiple llm provider support, go with CodeGPT. If auto-generates wiki from code matters more to you, Mutable AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
